### Description

**I have this custom directive :** 
import { Directive, HostListener, inject, Input} from '@angular/core';
import { MatTooltip } from '@angular/material/tooltip';

@Directive({
  selector: '[appCustomTooltip]',
  exportAs: 'appCustomTooltip',
  providers: [MatTooltip]
})
export class CustomTooltipDirective{

  @Input('appCustomTooltip') customTooltipText!: string;
  matTooltip = inject(MatTooltip);

  @HostListener('mouseover') mouseover() {
    this.matTooltip.message = this.customTooltipText;
    this.matTooltip.show();
  }
  @HostListener('mouseleave') mouseleave() {
      this.matTooltip.hide();
  }
}

**This worked for me because the custom directive was declared in the module and shares the context of the module (MatTooltipModule was imported in the module).**

Now I am trying to do the same thing with a standalone custom directive but it is not working because we do not have the option to import the **MatTooltipModule** in the context of the custom directive.


**I am trying to do this in order to use my standalone custom directive with the composition API directive.**






