### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Currently there is no way to reuse an existing pipe or service inside a standalone pipe. 

### Proposed solution

We should be able to specify providers for a pipe, just like we do for components and directives

```
@Pipe({
  name: 'formControlValue',
  providers: [DatePipe]
})
export class FormControlValuePipe implements PipeTransform {
  constructor(
    private datePipe: DatePipe
  ) {}

  transform(value: any, type: string) {
    switch (type) {
      case 'date':
        return this.datePipe.transform(value as string);
    }

    return value;
  }
}
```

### Alternatives considered

The only workardound available is using a non-standalone pipe:

```typescript
@NgModule({
  declarations: [FormControlValuePipe],
  exports: [FormControlValuePipe],
  providers: [DatePipe],
})
export class FormControlValueModule {}

@Pipe({
  name: 'formControlValue',
})
export class FormControlValuePipe implements PipeTransform {
  constructor(
    private datePipe: DatePipe
  ) {}

  transform(value: any, type: string) {
    switch (type) {
      case 'date':
        return this.datePipe.transform(value as string);
    }

    return value;
  }
}
```

However, this forces developers to abstain from using standalone pipes and sticking to otherwise redundant `NgModule`s.

### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

localize

### Description

Hi,

I am new to angular localize support. 
As translations now can be extracted to json format also , I have seen it does not support translation token as nested keys from json format file.

for example if below is the markup 
<span i18n="@@parent.child>
        Test translation 
</span>

and extracting it using json format like below generates messages.json file like bellow

ng extract-i18n --format=json --output-path src/locale

{
"parnet.child":"Test translation"
}

But, to group translation in logical manner shouldn't be like 
{
"parent":{
    "child": "Test translation "
}
}

Is there anything already present in framework to make it like above or not supported at all ?  

### Proposed solution

Should extract translation in json format to maintain logical grouping like below

 {
"parent":{
    "child": "Test translation "
}
}

